Package: PhyloSubset
Title: Phylogenetically Dispersed and Clustered Subset Selection
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("PhyloSubset", "Authors", email="phylosubset@example.com", role=c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Selects phylogenetically dispersed or clustered species subsets from a user-defined candidate pool and evaluates their distance-based dispersion and covariance-based dependence. Given a phylogenetic tree, a candidate species pool, and a target subset size, automatically selects dispersed or clustered subsets, computes distance metrics (MinPD, MeanPD, MeanNND, MaxPD), generates random baselines, calculates empirical p-values, and evaluates phylogenetic dependence diagnostics (MeanOffCor, MaxOffCor, MeanESS) under Brownian motion, Pagel's lambda, and Ornstein-Uhlenbeck covariance models.
